+## 4. Router - Select Among Alternatives
 
-The Router trait selects one Engram from a set of candidates and learns from outcomes.
+The Router trait chooses the best candidate and learns from outcomes. The revised design separates durable candidate sets from live candidate sets so both stored records and transport records can participate in routing.
 
-### 3.1 Trait Signature
+### 4.1 Recommended Signature
 
 ```rust
 pub trait Router: Send + Sync {
-    fn select(&self, candidates: &[Signal], ctx: &Context) -> Option<Selection>;
+    fn select_engram(&self, candidates: &[Engram], ctx: &Context) -> Option<Selection>;
+
+    fn select_pulse(&self, candidates: &[Pulse], ctx: &Context) -> Option<Selection> {
+        None
+    }
+
     fn feedback(&self, outcome: &Outcome);
-    fn name(&self) -> &str;
+    fn name(&self) -> &'static str;
