-## 5. Policy — React to Streams
+## 6. Policy - React To Pulses
 
-The Policy trait watches Engram streams and produces reactive interventions.
+Policy is the one trait whose shape changes in a breaking way. Its natural input is now a stream of Pulses, and its output is a structured bundle of Pulses and Engrams.
 
-### 5.1 Trait Signature
+### 6.1 Recommended Signature
 
 ```rust
 pub trait Policy: Send + Sync {
-    fn decide(&self, stream: &[Signal], ctx: &Context) -> Vec<Signal>;
-    fn name(&self) -> &str;
+    fn decide(&self, stream: &[Pulse], ctx: &Context) -> PolicyOutputs;
+    fn name(&self) -> &'static str;
+}
+
+pub struct PolicyOutputs {
+    pub pulses: Vec<Pulse>,
+    pub engrams: Vec<Engram>,
 }
 ```
 
-### 5.2 Key Implementations
+### 6.2 Why Policy Changes First
+
+Policy is the reactive layer. Reactive logic naturally consumes transport events, not only durable records. When a policy needs to react to stored material, that durable material should already have been surfaced as Pulses from the relevant fabric bridge. That keeps the source of truth clear: `Bus` carries live updates, `Substrate` stores durable outcomes.
 
-| Policy | Trigger | Emits |
-|---|---|---|
-| `CircuitBreakerPolicy` | Repeated gate failures | Pause/stop Engrams |
-| `EpisodeLogPolicy` | Agent turn completion | Episode Engrams |
-| `PheromonePolicy` | Market state changes | Pheromone Engrams |
-| `HeartbeatPolicy` | Timer tick | Heartbeat metric Engrams |
-| `AlertPolicy` | Tool health degradation | ToolHealthDegraded Engrams |
-| `EfficiencyPolicy` | Turn completion | Efficiency metric Engrams |
-| `ConductorPolicy` | Multiple signals | Conductor decisions |
+### 6.3 Typical Outputs
 
-### 5.3 Policy in the Loop
+- Emit Pulses for immediate reactions, notifications, or downstream routing.
+- Emit Engrams for durable summaries, consolidated decisions, or graduated stream content.
 
-Policy runs in step 8 (ADAPT) of the cognitive loop — after the gate verdict, after
-persistence, the Policy examines what just happened and emits reactions. Reactions are
-themselves Engrams, stored in the Substrate, and visible to subsequent loop ticks.
+### 6.4 Existing Policy Shapes
+
+- `CircuitBreakerPolicy` can watch gate verdict streams and publish pause Pulses.
+- `EpisodeLogPolicy` can turn turn-completion Pulses into episode records.
+- `HeartbeatPolicy` can publish clock Pulses at Gamma, Theta, and Delta cadence.
+- `EfficiencyPolicy` can emit durable metrics while also broadcasting live telemetry.
+
+### 6.5 Migration Note
+
+Policy is the only breaking change in this batch. The migration path for other operators is additive: existing Engram-oriented call sites can continue to work while Pulse-aware variants are introduced. Policy moves from `decide(&[Engram]) -> Vec<Engram>` to `decide(&[Pulse]) -> PolicyOutputs`, so callers need a structured adapter rather than a simple overload.
 
